Privacy Policy
Last updated: [17-Nov-25]
This privacy policy explains how Aurora, (“the Service”) collects, uses, and protects your information.
1.	Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how the service processes and handles information within the Discord server. By interacting with the service, users consent to the practices described here.
2.	Information the Service Processes
The service processes only the information necessary to perform its functions. This may include:
2.1 Automatically Processed Information
⦁	Discord User IDs
⦁	Server and channel IDs
⦁	Message content when required for specific actions
⦁	Reaction and interaction data
⦁	Ticket-related messages and metadata
2.2 Configuration Data
Certain server-specific settings (such as role IDs, channel references, or feature configurations) may be stored to maintain proper operation.
3.	Purpose of Data Processing
The service processes information solely to provide automated server management and communication features. This includes, but is not limited to:
⦁	Managing and organizing user interactions
⦁	Processing reactions, roles, and automated responses
⦁	Executing administrator-authorized commands
⦁	Performing server automation tasks as configured
The service does not use information for analytics, tracking, advertising, or any unrelated purpose.
4.	Data Storage and Retention
⦁	Only essential configuration data is stored persistently.
⦁	User-generated content processed during interactions is not stored long-term unless required for a feature (e.g., ticket logs).
⦁	Temporary data is cleared automatically once it is no longer needed.
⦁	No personal information outside of Discord-provided identifiers is collected or retained.
5.	Data Sharing and Disclosure
The service does not sell, share, or distribute any information to third parties.
Access to stored data is limited to:
⦁	The server owner
⦁	Authorized server administrators
No external individuals or organizations have access to the data processed by the service.
6.	User Rights
Users may request the following at any time, subject to server administrator approval:
⦁	Removal or deletion of stored data associated with them
⦁	Information about what data the service may process
⦁	Restrictions on future interactions with the service
⦁	Users who wish to avoid further processing may stop interacting with the service or leave the server.
7.	Security
Reasonable measures are taken to ensure that data processed by the service is handled securely and properly. However, no system is immune to potential vulnerabilities, and the service cannot guarantee absolute security.
8.	Changes to This Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated or revised at any time. Continued interaction with the service after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised Policy.
